<h3 id="rationale">
<a href="#rationale" class="anchor-link"></a> Rationale
</h3>
<p>This removes the need for implementations to have an explicit way to look into historical block hashes, simplifying the protocol definition and removing a large component of the ‚Äúimplied state‚Äù (information that is technically state but is not part of the state tree) and thereby making the protocol more ‚Äúpure‚Äù. Additionally, it allows blocks to directly point to blocks far behind them, which enables extremely efficient and secure light client protocols.</p>
